<P><font size="+1">Learning Plan 3 of 4 : Expressions and Formulae <Br><font size="-"></b></center>

<P>In Mathematics, symbols, in particular letters, are used to represent numbers eg.
<center> 2l + 2b.</center>
  This expression or formula, which calculates the perimeter of a rectangle, can be used over and over simply replacing the letters by numbers.  Meet this idea in Level 1 Lesson 13 <a href="runcal.htm#==//?~ 0 1 13 a~?">Section a</a>, <a href="runcal.htm#==//?~ 0 1 13 b 0~?">Section b</a>, <a href="runcal.htm#==//?~ 0 1 13 c~?">Section c</a>. 
<br>
Read   <a href="runcal.htm#==C:\\tcrun.exe C:\Version3\calpopup //?~ 0 1 13 f -2~?">Section f</a>, and do  <a href="runcal.htm#==C:\\tcrun.exe C:\Version3\calpopup //?~ 0 1 13 f 2~?">Tutorial 2 only</a>.  Now do questions  <a href="launch.htm#q0296">296</a>, <a href="launch.htm#q0297">297</a>, <a href="launch.htm#q0608">608</a> and <a href="launch.htm#q0653">653</a>. 
<br>You need to be able to deal with powers of numbers. Complete <a href="runcal.htm#== //?~ 0 1 14~?">Level 1 Lesson 14</a>, including the assessment. Then do questions  <a href="launch.htm#q0385">385</a>, <a href="launch.htm#q0388">388</a>, <a href="launch.htm#q0390">390</a>,  <a href="launch.htm#q0391">391</a>,  <a href="launch.htm#q0392">392</a>, <a href="launch.htm#q605">605</a>, <a href="launch.htm#q0606">606</a>, <a href="launch.htm#q0389">389</a>,  <a href="launch.htm#q0591">591</a>, <a href="launch.htm#q0549">549</a> and  <a href="launch.htm#q0649">649</a>. 
<P>Although Level 1 Lesson 13 <a href="runcal.htm#==//?~ 0 1 13 d~?">Section d</a> and <a href="runcal.htm#==//?~ 0 1 13 e 0~?">Section e</a> are not absolutely necessary at this stage you will find the content useful later in the course.
<br>
<P>Further useful formulae can be found in Lesson 19 <a href="runcal.htm#==//?~ 0 1 19 a~?">Section a</a> and <a href="runcal.htm#==//?~ 0 1 19 b 0~?">Section b</a>.
<br>
